Package: xraylib-oct%type_pkg[oct]
Version: 1.0.8
Type: oct (3.6.4), forge (xraylib), gcc (4.9)
Revision: 6
Distribution: 10.9, 10.10, 10.11, 10.12
Maintainer: Alexander Hansen <alexkhansen@users.sourceforge.net>
# unfortunately, Homepage won't do types
Homepage: http://octave.sourceforge.net/xraylib/index.html 
Description: Xraylib bindings for Octave
DescDetail: <<
Bindings to the Xraylib functions

This package provides the following functions:
        AtomicWeight
        CosKronTransProb
        CS_FluorLine
        EdgeEnergy
        LineEnergy
        FluorYield
        JumpFactor
        DCSP_Rayl
        DCSP_Compt
        DCSP_KN
        DCSP_Thoms
        RadRate
        FF_Rayl
        SF_Compt
        DCS_Thoms
        DCS_KN
        DCS_Rayl
        DCS_Compt
        MomentTransf
        CS_KN
        ComptonEnergy
        CS_Total
        CS_Photo
        CS_Rayl
        CS_Compt
        CSb_FluorLine
        CSb_Total
        CSb_Photo
        CSb_Rayl
        CSb_Compt
        DCSb_Rayl
        DCSb_Compt
        DCSPb_Rayl
        DCSPb_Compt
<<

License: GPL2

BuildDepends: <<
  liboctave%type_pkg[oct]-dev,
  fftw3,
  hdf5.9,
  xraylib,
  fink-octave-scripts (>= 0.3.0-1)
<<
Depends: <<
  octave%type_pkg[oct]-interpreter,
  xraylib-shlibs
<<
Conflicts: octave-forge

Source: mirror:sourceforge:octave/%type_raw[forge]-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: 2a3d14aa3c3f714e8782a54593ee9129

PatchScript:  <<
perl -pi -e    's|-I\./xraylib/src|-I%p/include/xraylib|; \
				s|-L\./xraylib/src|-L%p/lib|; \
				s|.*inline||' src/Makefile
<<

NoSetCPPFLAGS: true
NoSetLDFLAGS: true
UseMaxBuildJobs: false
BuildAsNobody: false

CompileScript: <<
#!/bin/sh -ev
pkgsrc=%type_raw[forge]-%v
##### Invariant stuff begins here #####
%p/share/fink-octave-scripts/octave-forge-patch.sh %type_raw[forge] %v %type_raw[oct] %b %i $pkgsrc
./octave-forge-compile.sh
<<

InstallScript: ./octave-forge-install.sh
PostInstScript:  %p/share/octave/%type_raw[oct]/%type_raw[forge]/octave-forge-postinst.sh
PreRmScript: %p/share/octave/%type_raw[oct]/%type_raw[forge]/octave-forge-prerm.sh

DescPackaging: <<
This package:
By default it rolls its own xraylib, but that wasn't working; building against an
external xraylib worked just fine.

Common for all octave-forge packages:
Preinst and postinst scripts are dynamically set up via 
%p/share/fink-octave-scripts/octave-forge-patch.sh because Octave's package manager 
can't cope with non-literal arguments.

The Type: forge (pkgname) is used to minimize what needs to be changed when
using this .info file as a template, or when the package name contains 
underscores.
<<
<<
